etical proposition that using different cosmological\ndistance measures in statistical analyses of galaxy surveys can lead to\nsignificant ambiguity in drawing conclusions about the behavior of the observed\nlarge scale distribution of galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Nov 2006 19:22:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
